=Short bio=

George Dafermos is a 'copyleft activist', a member of the [http://www.commonslab.gr Commons|Lab] open technology co-op and a researcher affiliated with the P2P Foundation. He holds a PhD from Delft University of Technology and is an internationally-known researcher and thinker on issues related to the governance of the commons, the mode of peer production, the role of users in the innovation process, open licensing and new organizational structures enabled by the Internet. His personal website is accessible at http://georgedafermos.github.io

